<OrgName><entry>BLUE BADGE SCHEME</entry>
</OrgName>
<Desc><entry>Allows parking without charge within a 3 hour time limit in Pay and Display parking bays on the street, in Council car parks and some limited parking on yellow lines, unless a ban on loading applies.  The scheme is for passengers who are registered blind and drivers or passengers with a permanent disability who have considerable difficulty in walking, those who are in receipt of the higher rate of the mobility component of Disability Living Allowance or drive an adapted car provided by the Department of Work and Pensions.</entry>
</Desc>
